<TITLE> BCIC victims identified </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 28 (bdnews24.com)--A mysterious explosion that triggered a blaze spreading across the second floor of BCIC Sadan in Motijheel Monday morning left one dead and seven people injured so far, police said. The dead was identified as Noor-e-Maleque Md Mojibur Rahman, our DMCH correspondent said. Fire fighters rescued four more people from the fourth floor of the building in the second spell of rescue operation, of whom one died. At around 11:40 am, the four unconscious people were evacuated. They had been asleep there. They fell ill as the fire smoke billowed and crept onto the fourth floor. The unconscious persons were soon sent to hospital, where one died. No one could be identified then and there. Dr Samanta Lal, physician on duty at the burn unit of Dhaka Medical College Hospital, said Noor-e-Maleque Md Mojibur Rahman had expired at around 11:15 am in unconscious state. Mojibur, hailing from Kishoreganj, was an employee of Ghorhasal Fertiliser Factory. He was the general secretary of Sramik League unit there. The injured Motaleb Chowdhury, 40, Md Shaheen, 30, Shiblu Saha, 28, Ujjal, 36, Rubel, 18, SM Anwar Hossain, 32 and Abdul Khaleque were sent to Dhaka medical College Hospital. Earlier in the morning firefighters had rescued four injured people from scene of the explosion that occurred on the second floor of the building. The total number of injured is now seven, police said. The firefighters doused the blaze at around 10:45 am. None could, however, ascertain as to how the explosion occurred. Immediately after the explosion, RAB, police and fire service personnel arrived at the spot and took up positions. People were also found thronging the spot. Police and fire brigade personnel said the blaze is now under control. bdnews24.c
